"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-culture-archive-2024-07-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-679270\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The city seemed exhausted, not exuberant.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 41, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Listen to more stories on theNoaapp.\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 79, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more stories\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 65}, {\"ngram\": \"theNoaapp\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 78}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, that was a nice idea in theory.\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a nice idea\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"theory\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris held the first-ever Olympics opening ceremony to take place outside a stadium-and on one of the loveliest settings in the world, the Seine.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2772001112482103e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.06875239220952e-28, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first-ever Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 170}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"the loveliest settings\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 239}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes paraded not by foot but by boat, waving flags from sleek cruising pontoons, as pageantry unfolded on bridges and riverbanks.\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"foot\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"boat\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 305}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"sleek cruising pontoons\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 348}, {\"ngram\": \"pageantry\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 362}, {\"ngram\": \"bridges\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"riverbanks\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The aquatic format promised to do more than just showcase the architectural beauty of Paris or convey the magic of strolling across the Pont Neuf with fresh bread in hand.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2772001112482103e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The aquatic format\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 417}, {\"ngram\": \"the architectural beauty\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"the magic\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont Neuf\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 544}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh bread\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 561}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 569}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It promised to offer the world-our ever more jaded, content-drowned world-something new to look at.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, that new thing was a mess.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"new thing\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"a mess\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some will blame the rain, which soaked the festivities for hours, adding an air of tragedy as athletes waved flags from within their ponchos.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rain\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"the festivities\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"an air\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"tragedy\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 828}, {\"ngram\": \"their ponchos\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even on a sunnier day, the ceremony would have served as an example of how not to stage a spectacle for live TV.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sunnier day\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"an example\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"a spectacle\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"live TV\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The energy was low, the pacing bizarre, and the execution patchy.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The energy\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"the execution patchy\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris tried to project itself as a modern, inclusive hub of excitement-but it mostly just seemed exhausted.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2772001112482103e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a modern, inclusive hub\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"excitement\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics opening ceremonies are inevitably ridiculous affairs, usually in a fun way.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics opening ceremonies\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"ridiculous affairs\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"a fun way\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The host nation must welcome the global community while cobbling all of the signifiers of its own identity into some sort of romping medley that also, ideally, expands that country's image in helpful ways.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The host nation\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"the global community\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1282}, {\"ngram\": \"the signifiers\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"its own identity\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"some sort\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"medley\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"that country's image\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1421}, {\"ngram\": \"helpful ways\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"London offered the Queen and James Bond, and also a tribute to the National Health Service.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997183672745, \"rank\": 2.8163252777145857e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2779634532425088e-13, \"text\": \"James Bond\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.343075437885715e-13, \"text\": \"National Health Service\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Queen\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"a tribute\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rio hosted a rumbling dance party as well as a briefing on Brazil's Indigenous history.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999920328264, \"rank\": 7.967221942504217e-09, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999992851315083, \"rank\": 4.532160859507519e-07, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rumbling dance party\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"a briefing\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most important, both of those cities gave us good TV.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those cities\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"good TV\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beforehand, the Paris event's artistic director, Thomas Jolly, announced his intentions to play with Gallic clich\\u00e9s.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2772001112482103e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", 